參照以上例子，用用廣東話「睇怕」一詞，造10句廣東話例句，然後寫英文嘅翻譯。

ASSISTANT: 1. 嗰個嘢真係好威，我睇怕到都唔敢近嚟。 (That thing is really scary, I'm so scared that I don't dare to go near it.)
   English Translation: That thing is really terrifying, I'm too scared to approach it.

2. 小朋友睇怕鬼，每當講到鬼就唔停地哭。 (Children are afraid of ghosts, they cry non-stop whenever ghosts are mentioned.)
   English Translation: Kids are scared of ghosts, they burst into tears whenever ghosts are mentioned.

3. 你睇怕靈魂嘅嗰啦嗰啦個？我覺得佢嚟同電影裡面嘅唔差。 (Are you scared of that thing about spirits? I think it's as good as the ones in the movies.)
   English Translation: Are you scared of that stuff about spirits? I think it's just as good as what's in the movies.

4. 我嘅貓睇怕煙響，每次聽到爆竹聲就躲樓下去。 (My cat is afraid of fireworks, every time it hears the sound of firecrackers, it hides under the bed.)
   English Translation: My cat is scared of fireworks, it always hides under the bed whenever it hears them.

5. 你睇怕唔睇怕，點解唔想試試咗遊樂場嘅極速迴旋？ (Whether you're scared or not, why don't you want to try the roller coaster at the amusement park?)
   English Translation: Whether you're scared or not, why don't you want to give the roller coaster at the amusement park a shot?

6. 我睇怕蟲，每當跌見螞蟻就唔停地拍手。 (I'm afraid of bugs, whenever I see ants, I clap my hands non-stop.)
   English Translation: I'm scared of bugs, I clap my hands constantly whenever I see ants.

7. 你睇怕黑暗嘅，夜晚唔覺得可怕？ (Are you scared of the dark? Don't you find the night frightening?)
   English Translation: Are you scared of the dark? Do you not find the night scary?

8. 佢睇怕醫院，一聽到要去醫院就嚇呆了。 (He's scared of hospitals, as soon as he hears he has to go to the hospital, he's terrified.)
   English Translation: He's scared of hospitals, he gets terrified as soon as he hears he has to go to one.

9. 我睇怕高度，站在高處就覺得好心慌。 (I'm afraid of heights, I get really nervous standing at a high place.)
   English Translation: I'm scared of heights, I get really anxious when I'm at an elevated spot.

10. 你睇怕唔睇怕，話唔話都想同佢咁近？ (Whether you're scared or not, do you really want to get so close to it?)
    English Translation: Regardless of whether you're scared or not, do you really want to get that close to it?</s>